declarations.comments:
Coords are an alias for pairs of numbers, more or less matching the `Position`
type alias in turf.
declarations.title: Coord

declarations.comments: A `Feature a` represents a GeoJSON feature with geometry of type `a`.
declarations.title: Feature

declarations.comments:
FeatureProperties represent the JSON object that GeoJSON features
have in their `properties` field.
declarations.title: FeatureProperties

declarations.comments:
Since `turf` returns features from all of its helper methods, it's convenient
to have a short-hand for getting the geometry back out.
declarations.title: featureGeometry

declarations.comments: A `LineStringGeom` is at least two points forming a linestring.
declarations.title: LineStringGeom

declarations.comments: A `LineStringFeature` is a `Feature` with geometry of type `LineStringGeom`
declarations.title: LineStringFeature

declarations.comments: Construct a `LineStringFeature` using the @turf/helpers `lineString` method
declarations.title: lineString

declarations.comments: A `MultiLineStringGeom` is a collection of unrelated LineStringGeoms
declarations.title: MultiLineStringGeom

declarations.comments: A `MultiLineStringFeature` is a `Feature` with geometry of type `MultiLineStringGeom`
declarations.title: MultiLineStringFeature

declarations.comments: Construct a `MultiLineStringFeature` using the @turf/helpers `multiLineString` method
declarations.title: multiLineString

declarations.comments: A `PointGeom` is nothing more than a newtype over `Coords`
declarations.title: PointGeom

declarations.comments: A `PointFeature` is a `Feature` with geometry of type `PointGeom`
declarations.title: PointFeature

declarations.comments: Construct a `PointFeature` using the @turf/helpers `point` method
declarations.title: point

declarations.comments: A `MultiPointGeom` represents a collection of un-connected `PointGeoms`
declarations.title: MultiPointGeom

declarations.comments: A `MultiPointFeature` is a `Feature` with geometry of type `MultiPointGeom`
declarations.title: MultiPointFeature

declarations.comments: Construct a `MultiPointFeature` using the @turf/helpers `multiPoint` method
declarations.title: multiPoint

declarations.comments:
A `LinearRing` is a collection of at least four points where the first and last
points are the same.
declarations.title: LinearRing

declarations.comments:
Construct a linear ring from the first three points and the remaining points.
This method ensures that if you've failed to match the first and last points,
a correct last point will be appended for you.
declarations.title: mkLinearRing

declarations.comments:
A `PolygonGeom` represents an exterior with possibly zero holes.
Note that nothing forbids you from making holes _outside_ the polygon.
@turf/helpers `polygon` method also doesn't get mad about this, so
while it doesn't really make sense, it's technically allowed.
declarations.title: PolygonGeom

declarations.comments: A `PolygonFeature` is a `Feature` with geometry of type `PolygonGeom`
declarations.title: PolygonFeature

declarations.comments: Construct a `PolygonFeature` using the @turf/helpers `polygon` method
declarations.title: polygon

declarations.comments: A `MultiPolygonGeom` represents a collection of `PolygonGeoms`.
declarations.title: MultiPolygonGeom

declarations.comments: A `MultiPolygonFeature` is a `Feature` with geometry of type `MultiPolygonGeom`
declarations.title: MultiPolygonFeature

declarations.comments: Construct a `MultiPolygonFeature` using the @turf/helpers `multiPolygon` method
declarations.title: multiPolygon
